===Etymology===
From {{inh|en|enm|thrīce}}, {{m|enm|thries||three times, thrice; a third time; repeated three times}},<ref>{{R:MED Online|entry=thrīce, adv.|id=MED45495|accessdate=13 May 2018}}</ref> from earlier {{m|enm|thrī}}, {{m|enm|thrīe||three times, thrice; a third time}} (from {{inh|en|ang|þriwa}}, {{m|ang|þreowa}})<ref>{{R:MED Online|entry=thrī(e, adv.|id=MED45503|accessdate=13 May 2018}}</ref> + {{m|enm|-es||''suffix forming adverbs of time, place, and manner''}} (from {{der|en|ang|-es||''suffix forming adverbs''}}).<ref>{{R:MED Online|entry=-es, suf.(1)|id=MED14416|accessdate=13 May 2018}}</ref> The word is cognate with {{cog|stq|träie||thrice}}.

